    "body": "### Problem\n\nI would be good if all affected windows by the resize are actually reported, this is also something that might be affected by things like `equalalways` and other window settings which might modify the layout or window sizes to keep them proportioal.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. nvim -u repro.lua\n2. resize the vertical portion of the terminal window left-right, such that technically both horizontal splits are changing their width, while the height remains constant.\n3. observe that only one window that is showing one of the buffers is showing in the logs instead of both of the windows.\n\n\n```lua\nlocal bufnr = vim.api.nvim_create_buf(false, false)\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"WinResized\", {\n    pattern = \"*\",\n    callback = function(args)\n        vim.print(args.buf)\n    end,\n})\nvim.print(bufnr)\nvim.cmd.split()\nvim.api.nvim_win_set_buf(0, bufnr)\n\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nTechnically both windows are getting resized, but only one window even is reported.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nmaster\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNot tested\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nubuntu\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nrelesae ",
